title: 17-year-old shot multiple times in N.O. East
text:
NEW ORLEANS, LA (WVUE) - Police are investigating the Thursday night shooting of a 17-year-old male in New Orleans East.
Just after 8:30, police said they learned that the victim had been shot multiple times near Dwyer Road and Crowder Boulevard. He arrived at the hospital in a private car.
Detectives were in the process of locating a scene and getting information on a suspect.
The victim's injuries are thought to be non-life-threatening.
